Peel and very finely chop @onion{1/2}(finely chopped) and all the @garlic{1%clove}(finely chopped). Chop the @cauliflower{1/2}(cut into bite-sized florets). Roughly chop the @coriander{2}(roughly chopped). Chop your @green beans{1}(chopped into thirds) and discard the ends.

Heat @oil{1%tbsp} in a large #pot on medium-low heat. Add the onion and garlic and slowly cook for ~{5%minutes}. Season with @salt{1/4%tsp} and a few grinds of @pepper{}. 

> Tip: If the onion starts to brown off turn the heat down a bit.

Once the onions are soft add the @curry powder mix{1} and stir.

Stir in the @tomato puree{1} and then add the @chopped tomatoes{1}(tinned). Add another @salt{1/4%tsp} and @?sugar{1/4%tsp}. Add the @red split lentils{1/2}(red split lentils), @water{200%ml} and half the @vegetable stock pot{1/2}. Bring to a gentle bubble, put on a #lid and leave for ~{5%minutes}.

Remove the lid and add the cauliflower. Cook for around ~{10%minutes} or until the cauliflower is tender.

When the cauliflower is halfway through cooking add the green beans and cook for ~{5%minutes} more.

> Tip: Don't worry if the dal is drying out a little – just add a bit more water to get a looser consistency.

Stir through @coriander{1%tbsp}(chopped) and @Greek style yoghurt{3%tbsp}.

> Tip: At this stage it's crucial to taste for seasoning - have a spoonful and add more salt and pepper to lift the flavours to their max!

Serve with a little more coriander and a nice big dollop of @Greek style yoghurt{1/2%tbsp}.